cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the development of a realistic dataset for network intrusion detection and network forensic systems in the context of IoT systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of statistical and machine learning methods for forensics purposes, which suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The dataset is specifically designed for IoT networks, indicating the relevance of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. Finally, the paper also mentions the evaluation of the dataset using different methods, which could be related to cs.SE (Software Engineering) category.
